  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QA/QC Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop, implement, and maintain project-specific QA/QC plans, ITPs (Inspection and Test Plans), and procedures aligned with ISO standards and client requirements.</li>\n  <li>Manage quality inspections, testing, and documentation throughout all phases of construction, including civil, structural, architectural, MEP, and commissioning stages.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with internal teams, subcontractors, and consultants to ensure compliance with design specifications and industry standards. (CONQUAS will be an advantage)</li>\n  <li>Oversee the inspection process for material receiving, in-progress works, mock-ups, and final handover.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with clients, authorities, and third-party inspectors (if any) during audits and site inspections.</li>\n  <li>Lead non-conformance reporting (NCR), root cause analysis, and implementation of corrective/preventive actions.</li>\n  <li>Ensure quality documentation, checklists, and test records are accurately maintained and handed over.</li>\n  <li>Support project commissioning and validation processes, particularly in controlled environments.</li>\n  <li>Provide training and guidance to site QA/QC personnel to uphold consistent quality practices.</li>\n  <li>Participate in risk assessments, method statement reviews, and quality-related meetings.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma with at least 5 years of experience in project/engineering/construction management, preferably in data centre or critical environment.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of ISO policies, QA/QC procedures, and international quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with MEP systems, containment, cleanroom classification and critical utility systems is an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in documentation control, audit preparation, and quality tracking tools.</li>\n  <li>Positive proactive attitude and ethical behaviour.</li>\n  <li>Good leadership and team player with ability to work independently and resolve challenges in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal, communication, collaborative and people management skills.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint).</li>\n</ul>",
